abstract_summ: A 36-year-old, gravida 2, para 1 woman positive for COVID-19 at 23 weeks of gestation with severe disease required admission to the intensive care unit and intubation . She completed 5 days of hydroxychloroquine and 7 days of prednisone . She was successfully intubated after 8 days and discharged home in a stable condition without preterm delivery .
